This paper discusses updating the generator in a generative adversarial network (GAN) architecture for image generation, specifically using the Progressive Growing of GANs (PPGAN) framework. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper involves updating the generator using gradients flowing through the encoder, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE). Finally, the paper may also involve natural language processing (cs.CL) if the generated images are used for text-to-image tasks.
